      "writtenOn": "2026-06-12T06:56:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This concatenation wouldn\u0027t work either, just tested for `javamelody` and `oauth` plugins.\n\nEach `external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel` declares:\n\n```python\nmaven \u003d use_extension(\"@rules_jvm_external//:extensions.bzl\", \"maven\")\n```\n\nIf two (or more) `external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel` are concatenated, then the build would fail:\n\n```\nERROR: /Users/Davido/projects/gerrit/plugins/external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel:30:1: \u0027maven\u0027 redeclared at top level\nERROR: /Users/Davido/projects/gerrit/plugins/external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel:11:1: \u0027maven\u0027 previously declared here\n```\n\nNote, that there is a documented way to build multiple plugins in gerrit tree with external dependencies, see `Documentation/dev-build-plugins.txt`, quoting:\n\nFor example, to import external dependencies for the `oauth` and `javamelody`\nplugins, add the following lines to `plugins/external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel`:\n\n```python\ninclude(\"//plugins/javamelody:external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel\")\ninclude(\"//plugins/oauth:external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel\")\n```\n\nIt should be easily doable to conduct new `plugins/external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel` with this content.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 113,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 113,
        "endChar": 202
      },
